title: lemon cake
description: its pretty good
source: my dads friend
---
§recipe
  §ingredients
	300g flour
	250ml milk (can be substituted with plant milk)
	200g sugar
	125g butter
	1 sachet baking powder
	1 sachet vanilla sugar
	2 lemons worth of juice
	For the icing:
	1 lemon of lemon juice
	icing sugar
  §/ingredients

  §instructions
	Preheat the oven to 180°C top/bottom heat.
	Place all the ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well until the batter is creamy. The batter is quite runny.
	Place baking paper on a baking tray and pour the batter onto it
	Bake the cake at 180°C for approx. 20 minutes. Test with a toothpick. If no more batter sticks to the toothpick, the cake is ready to be taken out.
	For the icing, squeeze a lemon and add in icing sugar until its thick like icing. Brush the cooled cake with it.
  §/instructions
§/recipe
